This topic is an overview of Kubernetes Service Manager for PCF.

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

Kubernetes Service Manager for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) enables platform operators
to provide application developers with access to services through the Marketplace.
These services run on Pivotal Container Service (PKS) for consumption by Pivotal Application Services (PAS) apps.

For more information about the Marketplace,
see [Pivotal Services Marketplace](https://pivotal.io/platform/services-marketplace).
For more information about PKS, see [Pivotal Container Service (PKS)](https://pivotal.io/platform/pivotal-container-service).

Kubernetes Service Manager for PCF enables platform operators to do the following:

* Install an Independent Software Vendor (ISV) or open source Helm chart into a PKS cluster.
* Offer an Independent Software Vendor (ISV) or open source Helm chart as on demand service to PAS developers.

Kubernetes Service Manager for PCF enables application developers to do the following:

* Provision dedicated service instances onto a PKS cluster through the Marketplace.
* Consume services running on Pivotal Container Service (PKS) in applications running on Pivotal Application Service (PAS).

## <a id='features'></a> Key Features

Kubernetes Service Manager for PCF includes the following key features:

* A service broker that provisions dedicated service instances into a PKS cluster and binds service instances to Pivotal Application Service (PAS) applications.
* A command line interface for managing service offerings and installing a shared service instance into a cluster.

